      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 180°C conventional (160°C fan). Whisk together the olive oil, sugar, orange zest, orange juice, and brandy. Add the flour, semolina, baking powder, bicarbonate of soda, and spices and mix to a soft, non-sticky dough. If the dough is sticky, add flour by the tablespoon. Shape into small oval patties about 4 cm long (20 to 22 g each), pressing a fork along the top to mark a pattern, and place on lined baking trays.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until firm and deep golden. While they bake, make the syrup: combine the honey, water, sugar, and cinnamon stick in a saucepan, bring to a boil, and simmer for 5 minutes. Keep warm.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Working in batches, dip the hot biscuits into the warm syrup for 20 to 30 seconds, turning once. Lift out with a slotted spoon and place on a rack. Scatter the finely chopped walnuts and a pinch of cinnamon over each while the syrup is still tacky. Leave to cool completely before storing. They keep for 10 to 14 days at room temperature.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
